# Brotherhood Portal Database (PostgreSQL)

## Overview

Primary database for the Brotherhood Portal.

Technology:

* PostgreSQL 16
* Entity Framework Core
* Docker Volume Persistence
* pgAdmin (optional)

Used for:

* Users / Identity
* Members
* Finance records
* Photos
* Invoice sequences
* Application data

---

# 1. Database Stack

Container Name:

```text
boena-postgres
```

Database Name:

```text
brotherhood_db
```

Default Port:

```text
5432
```

---

# 2. Environment Variables

```env
POSTGRES_DB=brotherhood_db
POSTGRES_USER=boena_postgres
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_STRONG_PASSWORD
```

---

# 3. Docker Commands

Start:

```bash
docker start boena-postgres
```

Stop:

```bash
docker stop boena-postgres
```

Logs:

```bash
docker logs boena-postgres
```

Shell:

```bash
docker exec -it boena-postgres bash
```

---

# 4. Connect with psql

```bash
docker exec -it boena-postgres psql -U boena_postgres -d brotherhood_db
```

Useful inside psql:

```sql
\l      -- list databases
\dt     -- list tables
\d tablename
SELECT * FROM "Members";
```

Exit:

```sql
\q
```

---

# 5. pgAdmin (Optional)

Container may exist:

```text
boena-pgadmin
```

Use browser UI to manage database.

Recommended server settings:

* Host: boena-postgres
* Port: 5432
* Username: boena_postgres
* Password: from `.env`

---

# 6. EF Core Migrations

Create migration:

```bash
dotnet ef migrations add MigrationName --project Brotherhood_Portal.Infrastructure --startup-project Brotherhood_Portal.API
```

Apply:

```bash
dotnet ef database update --startup-project Brotherhood_Portal.API
```

Remove last migration:

```bash
dotnet ef migrations remove
```

---

# 7. Auto Migrations

API may run migrations at startup.

Check logs:

```text
Applying database migrations...
Database migrations applied successfully.
```

---

# 8. Backups (Critical)

Create backup:

```bash
docker exec -t boena-postgres pg_dump -U boena_postgres brotherhood_db > backup.sql
```

Compressed backup:

```bash
gzip backup.sql
```

---

# 9. Restore Backup

```bash
cat backup.sql | docker exec -i boena-postgres psql -U boena_postgres -d brotherhood_db
```

If compressed:

```bash
gunzip -c backup.sql.gz | docker exec -i boena-postgres psql -U boena_postgres -d brotherhood_db
```

---

# 10. Persistent Storage

Docker volume example:

```yaml
volumes:
  postgres_data:
```

Never rely on container filesystem only.

---

# 11. Health Checks

Quick test:

```bash
docker exec boena-postgres pg_isready -U boena_postgres
```

Expected:

```text
accepting connections
```

---

# 12. Security Checklist

* [ ] Strong password
* [ ] Port 5432 not public unless required
* [ ] Backups scheduled
* [ ] Separate DB user per environment
* [ ] Keep PostgreSQL updated
* [ ] Restrict pgAdmin exposure

---

# 13. Common Queries

Count members:

```sql
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM "Members";
```

Latest finance rows:

```sql
SELECT * FROM "Finances" ORDER BY "CreatedAt" DESC LIMIT 10;
```

Users:

```sql
SELECT * FROM "AspNetUsers";
```

---

# 14. Troubleshooting

## Password Authentication Failed

Check `.env` password and container recreation.

## Connection Refused

Ensure container running:

```bash
docker ps
```

## Missing Tables

Run migrations.

## Volume Lost

Confirm named volume exists:

```bash
docker volume ls
```

---

# 15. Production Recommendations

* Nightly automated backups
* Weekly restore test
* Store backup off-server
* Monitor disk usage
* Use private Docker network only

---

# 16. Disaster Recovery

1. Install Docker
2. Start postgres container
3. Create database
4. Restore latest backup
5. Start API
6. Verify login and data

